      "id":"technology/2013/nov/07/russell-brand-iphone-ipad-app",
      "sectionId":"technology",
      "sectionName":"Technology",
      "webPublicationDate":"2013-11-07T09:05:56Z",
      "webTitle":"Russell Brand's official app offers fans chance to win one-to-one Skype chats",
      "webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/technology/2013/nov/07/russell-brand-iphone-ipad-app",
      "apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/technology/2013/nov/07/russell-brand-iphone-ipad-app",
      "fields":{
        "trailText":"British star joins Charlie Sheen, Jamie Foxx and Ty Lawson on the roster of apps startup TopFan. By <strong>Stuart Dredge</strong>",
        "headline":"Russell Brand's official app offers fans chance to win one-to-one Skype chats",
        "body":"<p>It's been a busy autumn for Russell Brand: getting <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/culture/2013/sep/13/russell-brand-gq-awards-hugo-boss\">ejected from the GQ awards</a>, touring <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/culture/2013/oct/13/russell-brand-messiah-complex-review\">his latest stand-up show</a>, <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/media/2013/nov/05/paxman-politics-russell-brand-voting\">sparring with Jeremy Paxman</a> on Newsnight and <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/world/2013/nov/06/protesters-gather-million-mask-march\">taking part in the Million Mask protest march</a>.</p> <p>Now he's setting his sights on a new target: success on the App Store. Brand has become the latest celebrity to release an official mobile app, through a partnership with tech startup <a href=\"http://top-fan.com/\">TopFan</a>. He joins actors Charlie Sheen and Jamie Foxx and basketball star Ty Lawson on the company's roster.</p> <p>Called simply <a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/gb/app/russell-brand/id733557559?mt=8\">Russell Brand</a>, the iPhone and iPad app &ndash; with Android likely to follow, judging by TopFan's previous releases &ndash; is fairly standard for its genre, with feeds of Brand's official posts on Twitter, Instagram and Facebook as well as photo and video galleries.</p> <p>It also invites people to compete in \"interactive fan challenges\" to win autographs, merchandise, meet-and-greets and other rewards from the star. Fans will earn points by completing the challenges &ndash; although none are yet available within the app &ndash; exchanging them for prizes.</p> <p>15,000 points will earn a copy of Brand's Scandalous live show, 40,000 points an autographed Rolling Stone magazine, and for fans keen enough to accumulate 500,000 points, they'll win a 10-minute Skype call with the star.</p> <p>Are celebrity apps just vanity projects? They can actually be decent money-spinners. Musician <a href=\"http://www.billboard.com/biz/articles/news/branding/1560642/how-trey-songzs-fan-club-app-earns-more-than-50k-a-month\">Trey Songz was making $50,000 a month</a> from his fan-app in May this year, with fans bidding to get their profile photos featured on its \"Instant VIP\" board.</p> <p>That app's developer, Handmade Mobile Entertainment, has been applying lessons learned from its Flirtomatic dating app to celebrities, working with Soulja Boy, Terrell Owens and The Only Way Is Essex's Mark Wright on similar apps.</p> <p>Also in May, <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/music/appsblog/2013/may/07/snoop-dogg-snoopify-app-instagram\">Snoop Dogg launched an app called Snoopify</a>, which fans could use to customise their photos with virtual stickers bought from an in-app shop.&nbsp;By June, the app was <a href=\"http://online.wsj.com/news/articles/SB10001424127887324069104578531820453319946\">selling $30,000 of stickers a week</a>, and by August <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/music/2013/aug/09/snoop-lion-spliff-smoke-app-snoopify\">included a $99.99 spliff as one of its options</a>, bought 15 times in its first week.</p> <p>That's not a strategy likely to appeal to the drug-free Brand, whose app's moneymaking is more about promoting his tour, books and films, while keeping fans up to date on his latest news and political views.</p><!-- Guardian Watermark: internal-code/content/421881068|2013-11-11T15:34:09Z|e259e369b033e1c38a4b4d6e76ac4ba7530c4eac -->",
